<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male</emphasis>
, wingspan 32-34 mm (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Adults of Sacada spp. 7 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), India 8 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), holotype, Sikkim, India 9 S. inordinata (Walker) (male), holotype, Darjeeling, India 10 S. dzonguensis, sp. nov. (male), India. 11 S. umtasorensis, sp. nov. (male), India 12 S. pallescens Hampson (male), India. Scale bars: 5 mm (7, 10, 11); 12.7 mm (12)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443710" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Adults of Sacada spp. 7 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), India 8 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), holotype, Sikkim, India 9 S. inordinata (Walker) (male), holotype, Darjeeling, India 10 S. dzonguensis, sp. nov. (male), India. 11 S. umtasorensis, sp. nov. (male), India 12 S. pallescens Hampson (male), India. Scale bars: 5 mm (7, 10, 11); 12.7 mm (12)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443710" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8</figureCitation>
). Adult pale rufous, speckled with fuscous; forewing pale brownish pink; basal and apical area of costa rufous; forewing with two black specks (lower one large, giving appearance of a spot) conjoined by a narrow bar; traces of evenly curved postmedial line, with area beyond it darker. Hindwing pale, with faint traces of a curved submarginal line. Cilia of both wings dark rufous. Blackish fringe of hair on fore and mid tibiae. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">26</figureCitation>
) with uncus short, broad with flaps on lateral side; gnathos well developed reaching to uncus, tip hooked; valva broad, simple, without any process; tegumen simple; transtilla with a sclerotised process arising medially; juxta double, each broad at base, apically pointed and sclerotised, concave on inner edge, convex on outer edge; saccus long, broadly U-shaped; vesica membranous with fine scobination, without any cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Sacada" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sacada unilinealis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unilinealis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Sacada unilinealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an unmistakable species due to the weak markings and almost uniform colour of the fore and hindwings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
